review_blob: While the beer had nice malty flavors when I first sipped it, I continually felt that it was lacking the oompf that would make this beer memorable.

When I poured this beer out of the bottle, I simply couldnt believe how dark it was. I actually held it up to a light to see if any shined through (none did). This was a dark, roasted beer with tastes of chocolate and coffee. Every sip brings about new flavors.
Had this beer on tap as a whim at a bar. The menu had it listed as an IPA, which it simply was not as it was lacking in any hoppy bitterness I could taste. It was a standard malty beer.
I found this to be a somewhat average IPA. Although not an exceptionally high abv, I found the bitterness of the alcohol took away from the bitterness of the hops.
As someone who is partial to wheat beers, I found this beer especially delicious. Simply a pleasant, crisp, and enjoyable beer.
Delicious IPA. In my opinion, as the beer warmed up in the glass, it became significantly more flavorful.
